HEADWORD: Mettlesome
<hw>Met"tle*some</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of spirit;
possessing constitutional ardor; fiery; <as>as, a <ex>mettlesome</ex>
horse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Met"tle*some*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Met"tle*some*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meum</ent>⟦br⟧
